.sg-subsection
  %h4 Togglable Tabs &amp; Pills
  %p.sg-twothird.pull To utilize a drop dead simple version of hiding and showing content related to a tab/pill, utilize <a href="http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/javascript.html#tabs">Bootstrap's Tab</a> plugin. The base structure of tabs and pills doesn't change, except to include a few more classes on the links and the <code>href</code> attribute the button will target.
  %pre.prettyprint
    = preserve do
      :escaped
        <nav>
          <ul class="nav tabs">
            <li>
              <a data-toggle="tab" href="#tab_one">Tab One</a>
            </li>
            <li class="active">
              <a data-toggle="tab" href="#tab_two">Tab Two</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </nav>
        <!-- tab-content holds all tab-pane markup -->
        <div class="tab-content">
          <div class="tab-pane" id="tab_one">
            <p>Tab one content</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab_two">
            <p>Tab two content</p>
          </div>
        </div>
  .notification.important.fade.in
    %p <strong>Note!</strong> When targeting pills, use <code>data-toggle="pill"</code> for links and <code>.pill-content</code>, <code>.pill-pane</code> for content elements.

